@startuml
title Sequence - Microbatch on one partition (Model A, per-key join-only, Kafka transactions)

participant "Partition Event Loop\n(single-thread)" as L
participant "Kafka Consumer" as C
participant "Tokens Codec" as D
participant "In-Memory Join State" as S
participant "Matcher" as M
participant "Rules Registry" as R
participant "Reactions Executor" as E
participant "Kafka Txn Producer" as P
database "Kafka Cluster\n(topic domain.tokens)" as K
participant "External System\n(HTTP/DB)" as X

== 1) Poll ==
L -> C: poll(maxRecords, timeout)
C -> K: Fetch records from assigned partition
K --> C: records r1..rn
C --> L: records r1..rn

== 2) Enqueue + incremental match ==
loop for each record ri
  L -> D: decode(ri) -> Token{key, channel_id, event_id, payload}
  D --> L: token ti
  L -> S: enqueue(ti.channel_id, ti.key, ti)
  L -> M: onTokenArrived(ti.channel_id, ti.key)

  M -> R: rulesByChannel[channel_id] -> worklist
  loop while worklist not empty
    M -> S: enabled?(rule R, key=ti.key)  // all deps non-empty for this key
    alt enabled
      M -> S: pop_front one token from each dep queue (FIFO)
      M -> E: scheduleFiring(ruleId, key, consumedTokens)
    else not enabled
      M -> M: continue
    end
  end
end

== 3) Execute scheduled firings ==
loop for each scheduled firing f (deterministic order)
  E -> E: reactionExecutionId = hash(ruleId, consumed event_ids)
  opt optional side effects
    E -> X: call(request, idempotencyKey=reactionExecutionId)
    X --> E: response
  end
  E -> E: outTokens += emitted tokens (each has key + channel_id + new event_id)
end

== 4) Transactional produce outputs + commit offsets ==
L -> P: beginTransaction()
P -> K: Begin producer transaction (transactional.id)
loop for each output token ot
  L -> D: encode(ot) -> kafkaMessage(key=ot.key, headers{channel_id,event_id}, value=payload)
  D --> L: msg
  L -> P: send(msg)
  P -> K: Produce message (part of txn)
end
L -> P: sendOffsetsToTransaction(offsets for r1..rn)
P -> K: Add offsets to txn
L -> P: commitTransaction()
P -> K: Commit txn (outputs become visible + offsets committed atomically)
K --> P: committed
P --> L: ok

note over L,K
If worker crashes before commit:
- transaction is aborted/never committed
- offsets are not committed
- records will be re-polled
- aborted outputs are not visible to read_committed consumers
end note

@enduml
